wiki.summary: "Good Ones" is the lead single from Charli XCX's fifth studio album, CRASH. The song turns away from the more experimental hyperpop-oriented production of her previous releases, returning to the poppier sound present earlier in her career. It was described as a synthwave and electropop song, filled with "hypnotic, throbbing synths" and "punchy production". Lyrically, the song depicts her habit to attract toxic relationships and sabotage healthy ones. Read more on Last.fm.
